SIMPLE: reduplication
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reduplication
<hw>Re*du`pli*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(-k?sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧duplication</ets>, L. <ets>reduplicatio</ets>
repetition.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of doubling, or the state of
being doubled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>A figure in which the first word
of a verse is the same as the last word of the preceding
verse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>The doubling of a stem or
syllable (more or less modified), with the effect of changing the time
expressed, intensifying the meaning, or making the word more imitative;
also, the syllable thus added; <as>as, L. <xex>te</xex>tuli;
<xex>po</xex>posci</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reduplicative</ent>⟦br⟧
